Loicque Hi,

We have reviewed page 6 of the Private Banking Tariff which covers
execution fees.

We must have earlier misunderstood some rough numbers that were verbally
mentioned to us, as the figures of 0.5%-1.0% for equity trading and
0.4%-0.6% for fixed interest trading (for roughly our size of transactions)
now seem much higher than we were prepared for.

Our family office's experience tells us that rates of 0.10-0.15% for equity
income trading; 0.08-0.12% for fixed income trading, and 0.10-0.15% for
custodianship are easily achievable with other institutions.

Are you able to provide such rates?

With thanks,

Adam

